  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>To his much and worthily esteemed
friend the Author.</head>
   <l>VVHo takes thy volume to his vertuous hand,</l>
   <l>Must be intended still to vnderstand:</l>
   <l>Who bluntly doth but looke vpon the same,</l>
   <l>May aske, <hi>what Author would conceale his name?</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Who reads may roaue, and call the passage darke,</l>
   <l>Yet may as blind men sometimes hit the marke.</l>
   <l>Who reads, who roaues, who hopes to vnderstand,</l>
   <l>May take thy volume to his vertuous hand.</l>
   <l>Who cannot reade, but onely doth desire</l>
   <l>To vnderstand, hee may at length admire.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>B. I.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
